The paper discusses the use of machine learning approaches in designing high-performance robots for flapping wing flight, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of automated design, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The study involves sim2real transfer, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of parameterised morphology design space, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV).
